<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<odoo>
    <!--
        Enable the "Variants" feature so the Owner can see and edit product
        Attributes in the backend (Sales / Website > Configuration > Attributes).

        WHY THIS IS NEEDED
        Odoo hides the Attributes menu behind the security group
        `product.group_product_variant`. On a brand-new database that group is
        granted to nobody, so even the admin cannot reach Attributes — which we
        need, because Coffin models are built from native product attributes
        (wood, handles...). The old demo seed switched this on as a side effect
        of creating attribute records; now that the demo is retired, a fresh DB
        loses it. This record turns it back on, the proper way, in code.

        HOW IT WORKS
        `base.group_user` is the group EVERY internal/backend user belongs to
        (the Owner included). A group can "imply" other groups via `implied_ids`
        — any member of this group automatically also gets the implied ones.
        We add `product.group_product_variant` to that list, so every backend
        user (i.e. the Owner) gains the Variants feature, and the Attributes
        menu shows up.

        eval="[(4, ref(...))]" is Odoo's command syntax for one2many/many2many
        fields: (4, id) means "LINK this existing record into the set" (without
        removing what's already there). `ref(...)` looks up the numeric id of a
        record from its xmlid.

        This is loaded as DATA (not demo), so it applies on every install AND on
        every `make reset` + reinstall — the durable fix the Owner asked for.
    -->
    <record id="base.group_user" model="res.groups">
        <field name="implied_ids" eval="[(4, ref('product.group_product_variant'))]"/>
    </record>
</odoo>
